    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    App
    The App class serves as the main entry point and manager for the Chess game application.
    Bishop
    Represents a bishop chess piece.
    Game
    Represents a chess game, including the board position, move history, and the current state of the game.
    Game.Color
    Enum representing the colors of the chess pieces.
    King
    Represents a king chess piece.
    Knight
    Represents a Knight piece in the game.
    Move
    Represents a move in a chess game, including details such as the start and end squares, the piece moved, move notation, and the resulting position after the move.
    Pawn
    Represents a Pawn piece in the game.
    Piece
    Represents a chess piece and provides methods for move validation, movement, capturing, and move notation.
    Player
    Represents a player in the game, which includes their color option and the color they are assigned to play.
    Player.ColorOption
    Enum representing the possible color options for a player.
    Position
    Represents the chessboard's position at any given time in the game.
    Queen
    Represents a Queen piece in the game of chess.
    Rook
    Represents a Rook piece in the game of chess.
    Square
    Represents a single square on the chessboard.
    Stockfish
    This class interacts with the Stockfish chess engine to make moves, get engine output, and manage its lifecycle.
